WILLIAM BUTLER DUNCAN et al., Plaintiffs, v. JACOB BERLIN et al., Defendants. Motion for judgment on a verdict directed for plaintiffs, subject to the opinion of the court at General Term, in an action brought to recover money paid to the sheriff on execution, in favor of defendants, by mistake.

Before Monell, Curtis, and Sedgwick, JJ.

Decided January 4, 1873. Wm. D. White, for plaintiffs. F. C. Cantine, for defendants.

Verdict set aside, and another trial ordered.

Opinion by Monell, J., Curtis and Sedgwick, JJ., concurring.
